<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Chess_strategy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BJohn_Nunn.5D.5D2001"><a href="/wiki/John_Nunn" title="John Nunn">John Nunn</a> (2001). <i>Understanding Chess Move by Move</i>. Gambit.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Understanding+Chess+Move+by+Move&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BJohn+Nunn%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BJohn+Nunn%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pub=Gambit&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Chess_strategy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> An <a href="/wiki/International_Grandmaster" title="International Grandmaster" class="mw-redirect">International Grandmaster</a> explains the thinking behind every single move of many world-class games.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BJeremy_Silman.5D.5D1999"><a href="/wiki/Jeremy_Silman" title="Jeremy Silman">Jeremy Silman</a> (1999). <i>The Amateur's Mind: Turning Chess Misconceptions into Chess Mastery</i>. Siles Press.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Amateur%27s+Mind%3A+Turning+Chess+Misconceptions+into+Chess+Mastery&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BJeremy+Silman%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BJeremy+Silman%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.pub=Siles+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Chess_strategy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> A chess teacher analyzes and corrects the thinking of advanced beginners.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJames_Eade2001">James Eade (2001). <i>Chess for Dummies</i>. Gambit.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Chess+for+Dummies&amp;rft.aulast=James+Eade&amp;rft.au=James+Eade&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pub=Gambit&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Chess_strategy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> A comprehensive guide for beginners.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BYasser_Seirawan.5D.5D2005"><a href="/wiki/Yasser_Seirawan" title="Yasser Seirawan">Yasser Seirawan</a> (2005). <i>Winning Chess Strategies</i>. Everyman Chess. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1857443853" class="internal">ISBN 1-85744-385-3</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Winning+Chess+Strategies&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BYasser+Seirawan%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BYasser+Seirawan%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pub=Everyman+Chess&amp;rft.isbn=1-85744-385-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Chess_strategy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
