<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Chess_strategy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.howtoadvice.com/Chess" class="external text" title="http://www.howtoadvice.com/Chess" rel="nofollow">64 Commandments of Chess</a> by <a href="/wiki/Bruce_Pandolfini" title="Bruce Pandolfini">Bruce Pandolfini</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.geocities.com/jmgruizus/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.geocities.com/jmgruizus/index.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Chess Strategy</i>, Second Edition</a> (also at <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/5614" class="external text" title="http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/5614" rel="nofollow">Gutenberg-project</a>), and <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/4913" class="external text" title="http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/4913" rel="nofollow"><i>Chess and Checkers: the Way to Mastership</i></a> by <a href="/wiki/Edward_Lasker" title="Edward Lasker">Edward Lasker</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/16377" class="external text" title="http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/16377" rel="nofollow"><i>The Blue Book of Chess</i></a>; "Teaching the Rudiments of the Game, and Giving an Analysis of All the Recognized Openings" by <a href="/wiki/Howard_Staunton" title="Howard Staunton">Howard Staunton</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.chesslodge.com" class="external text" title="http://www.chesslodge.com" rel="nofollow">Chess Strategy</a>, free lessons on basic elements.</li>
</ul>
